defs.name: average SAT score
defs.help: Average first-year student SAT score. SAT scores are currently on the 2400 scale until colleges release scores on the new 1600 scale in 2018.

gc_sort_def.name: Average SAT Score
gc_sort_def.help: Average first-year student SAT score. SAT scores are currently on the 2400 scale until colleges release scores on the new 1600 scale in 2018.

defs.name: Six-year Graduation Rate
defs.help: Graduation rate for bachelor's degree students within 150% of normal time.

defs.name: % of Freshmen on Any Aid
defs.help: Percent of full-time first-time undergraduates receiving any financial aid (grants or loans).

defs.name: Average Net Price
defs.help: Cost of attendance (including tuition and fees, books and supplies, and living expenses) minus federal, state, and institutional aid.
